                            <comment id="14489186" author="rsivaram" created="Fri, 10 Apr 2015 08:45:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Created reviewboard &lt;a href=&quot;https://reviews.apache.org/r/33071/diff/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://reviews.apache.org/r/33071/diff/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
 against branch origin/trunk&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14489201" author="rsivaram" created="Fri, 10 Apr 2015 08:58:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The attached patch dynamically loads the JRE-specific class for obtaining process CPU time. It could be made more efficient by caching the getProcessCpuTime method, but since it is only invoked twice, it seemed neater to keep all the code in a single method. Have also added code to get process CPU time for IBM JRE.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Compiled and ran code with OpenJDK which uses the class from com.sun package and with IBM JDK. Both compiled and printed out process CPU time.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14498339" author="junrao" created="Thu, 16 Apr 2015 17:27:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the patch. +1 and committed to trunk.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
